Get the input data

All the data can be downloaded from http://www-huber.embl.de. We use get the list of files from the wepage and, scrape them and then load them into the global environment.

base_url <- "http://www-huber.embl.de/pub/DEUprimates_supplement/SupplementaryFile3/objects"
r <- GET(base_url)
x <- content(r, type = "text/html")
## No encoding supplied: defaulting to UTF-8.
# html_structure(x)
potential_files  <- xml_text(xml_find_all(x, "//a"))
potential_files
